      "source": [
        "from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Import dataset\n",
        "data = pd.read_csv(\"amazon.csv\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YfmiWzZkcfMB"
      },
      "execution_count": 10,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Select relevant numerical columns and preprocess\n",
        "# Convert price columns to numeric values by removing non-numeric symbols and converting to float\n",
        "data['discounted_price'] = data['discounted_price'].replace({'₹': '', ',': ''}, regex=True).astype(float)\n",
        "data['actual_price'] = data['actual_price'].replace({'₹': '', ',': ''}, regex=True).astype(float)\n",
        "data['rating'] = pd.to_numeric(data['rating'], errors='coerce')\n",
        "data['rating_count'] = data['rating_count'].replace({',': ''}, regex=True).astype(float)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IqkGsr4ydDe4"
      },
      "execution_count": 11,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Drop any rows with missing values in these columns\n",
        "data = data[['discounted_price', 'actual_price', 'rating', 'rating_count']].dropna()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cfciueuIdGIc"
      },
      "execution_count": 12,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Scale the data for clustering\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(data)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Atgebc7-dKeQ"
      },
      "execution_count": 13,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Apply DBSCAN\n",
        "# Set eps (distance) and min_samples based on data density; these are adjustable.\n",
        "dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=0.5, min_samples=5)\n",
        "data['Cluster'] = dbscan.fit_predict(scaled_data)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OLbN50UldTI0"
      },
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Display the clustering results\n",
        "print(\"DBSCAN Clustering Results:\")\n",
        "print(data['Cluster'].value_counts())"
      ],
      "metadata": {

        "# Display a sample of the data with cluster labels\n",

        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Reduce dimensions to 2D for visualization using PCA\n",
        "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
        "data_pca = pca.fit_transform(scaled_data)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tQNFghx9fAcU"
      },
      "execution_count": 19,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Add PCA results to the dataframe for visualization\n",
        "data['PCA1'] = data_pca[:, 0]\n",
        "data['PCA2'] = data_pca[:, 1]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "TKy98y3XfMVZ"
      },
      "execution_count": 20,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Plot the clusters using the PCA components\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='PCA1', y='PCA2', hue='Cluster', palette='viridis', legend='full')\n",
        "plt.title(\"DBSCAN Clustering Visualization (PCA-reduced)\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Principal Component 1\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Principal Component 2\")\n",
        "plt.legend(title=\"Cluster\", loc=\"best\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
